{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:lamentations.3",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "lamentations",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Lamentations 3 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:1",
      "text": "I am the man who has seen affliction under the rod of his wrath;",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:2",
      "text": "he has driven and brought me into darkness without any light;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:3",
      "text": "surely against me he turns his hand again and again the whole day long.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:4",
      "text": "He has made my flesh and my skin waste away, and broken my bones;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:5",
      "text": "he has beseiged and enveloped me with bitterness and tribulation;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:6",
      "text": "he has made me dwell in darkness like the dead of long ago.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:7",
      "text": "He has walled me about so that I cannot escape; he has put heavy chains on me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:8",
      "text": "though I call and cry for help, he shuts out my prayer;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:9",
      "text": "he has blocked my ways with hewn stones, he has made my paths crooked.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:10",
      "text": "He is to me like a bear lying in wait, like a lion in hiding;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:11",
      "text": "he led me off my way and tore me to pieces; he has made me desolate;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:12",
      "text": "he bent his bow and set me as a mark for his arrow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:13",
      "text": "He drove into my heart the arrows of his quiver;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:14",
      "text": "I have become the laughingstock of all peoples, the burden of their songs all day long.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:15",
      "text": "He has filled me with bitterness, he has sated me with wormwood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:16",
      "text": "He has made my teeth grind on gravel, and made me cower in ashes;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:17",
      "text": "my soul is bereft of peace, I have forgotten what happiness is;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:18",
      "text": "so I say, “Gone is my glory, and my expectation from the Lord.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:19",
      "text": "Remember my affliction and my bitterness, the wormwood and the gall!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:20",
      "text": "My soul continually thinks of it and is bowed down within me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:21",
      "text": "But this I call to mind, and therefore I have hope:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:22",
      "text": "The steadfast love of the Lord never ceases, his mercies never come to an end;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:23",
      "text": "they are new every morning; great is thy faithfulness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:24",
      "text": "“The Lord is my portion,” says my soul, “therefore I will hope in him.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:25",
      "text": "The Lord is good to those who wait for him, to the soul that seeks him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:26",
      "text": "It is good that one should wait quietly for the salvation of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:27",
      "text": "It is good for a man that he bear the yoke in his youth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:28",
      "text": "Let him sit alone in silence when he has laid it on him;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:29",
      "text": "let him put his mouth in the dust— there may yet be hope;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:30",
      "text": "let him give his cheek to the smiter, and be filled with insults.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:31",
      "text": "For the Lord will not cast off for ever,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:32",
      "text": "but, though he cause grief, he will have compassion according to the abundance of his steadfast love;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:33",
      "text": "for he does not willingly afflict or grieve the sons of men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:34",
      "text": "To crush under foot all the prisoners of the earth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:35",
      "text": "to turn aside the right of a man in the presence of the Most High,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:36",
      "text": "to subvert a man in his cause, the Lord does not approve.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.37",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:37",
      "text": "Who has commanded and it came to pass, unless the Lord has ordained it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.38",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:38",
      "text": "Is it not from the mouth of the Most High that good and evil come?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.39",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:39",
      "text": "Why should a living man complain, a man, about the punishment of his sins?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.40",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:40",
      "text": "Let us test and examine our ways, and return to the Lord!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.41",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:41",
      "text": "Let us lift up our hearts and hands to God in heaven:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.42",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:42",
      "text": "“We have transgressed and rebelled, and thou hast not forgiven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.43",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:43",
      "text": "“Thou hast wrapped thyself with anger and pursued us, slaying without pity;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.44",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:44",
      "text": "thou hast wrapped thyself with a cloud so that no prayer can pass through.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.45",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:45",
      "text": "Thou hast made us offscouring and refuse among the peoples.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.46",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:46",
      "text": "“All our enemies rail against us;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.47",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:47",
      "text": "panic and pitfall have come upon us, devastation and destruction;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.48",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:48",
      "text": "my eyes flow with rivers of tears because of the destruction of the daughter of my people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.49",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:49",
      "text": "“My eyes will flow without ceasing, without respite,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.50",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:50",
      "text": "until the Lord from heaven looks down and sees;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.51",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:51",
      "text": "my eyes cause me grief at the fate of all the maidens of my city.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.52",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 52,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:52",
      "text": "“I have been hunted like a bird by those who were my enemies without cause;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.53",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 53,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:53",
      "text": "they flung me alive into the pit and cast stones on me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.54",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 54,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:54",
      "text": "water closed over my head; I said, ‘I am lost.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.55",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 55,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:55",
      "text": "“I called on thy name, O Lord, from the depths of the pit;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.56",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 56,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:56",
      "text": "thou didst hear my plea, ‘Do not close thine ear to my cry for help!’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.57",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 57,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:57",
      "text": "Thou didst come near when I called on thee; thou didst say, ‘Do not fear!’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.58",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 58,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:58",
      "text": "“Thou hast taken up my cause, O Lord, thou hast redeemed my life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.59",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 59,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:59",
      "text": "Thou hast seen the wrong done to me, O Lord; judge thou my cause.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.60",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 60,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:60",
      "text": "Thou hast seen all their vengeance, all their devices against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.61",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 61,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:61",
      "text": "“Thou hast heard their taunts, O Lord, all their devices against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.62",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 62,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:62",
      "text": "The lips and thoughts of my assailants are against me all the day long.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.63",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 63,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:63",
      "text": "Behold their sitting and their rising; I am the burden of their songs.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.64",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 64,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:64",
      "text": "“Thou wilt requite them, O Lord, according to the work of their hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.65",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 65,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:65",
      "text": "Thou wilt give them dullness of heart; thy curse will be on them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.3.66",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 66,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:66",
      "text": "Thou wilt pursue them in anger and destroy them from under thy heavens, O Lord.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
